# Code Style Guide

*This rule is automatically attached when working with code files. Customize it with your specific coding style preferences.*

## General Principles

- Follow the style guide defined in `docs/STYLE_GUIDE.md`
- Maintain consistency with existing code patterns
- When in doubt, look at similar files in the codebase
- Prefer clarity over cleverness

## Before Writing Code

1. Review existing similar files to understand patterns
2. Check `docs/STYLE_GUIDE.md` for language-specific guidelines
3. Ensure your code matches the project's naming conventions
4. Follow the established error handling patterns
5. Include appropriate comments and documentation

## Code Review Checklist

- [ ] Follows naming conventions
- [ ] Matches formatting style
- [ ] Includes appropriate error handling
- [ ] Has necessary comments/documentation
- [ ] Follows architectural patterns
- [ ] Includes tests if applicable

